M|ANAL|> Lo|producing any data al, writing the ce brief data section, diagnosing a metric anomaly, or establishing baselines.
M|ANAL|tx|---
M|Cont|Befo|
M|Cont|tx|1. Active vt (nz or hb)
M|Cont|tx|2. `last_data_pull_date` from memory — if > 14 days ago, flag data may be stale
M|Cont|tx|3. `baseline_*` keys from memory — what are we comparing against?
M|Cont|tx|4. `tracked_anomalies` from memory — are there known issues to account for?
M|Cont|tx|If data is stale, flag it before producing al. Never present stale data as current.
M|Cont|tx|---
M|Soci|tx|\| Metric \| Definition \| Measured By \|
M|Soci|tx|\|--------\|-----------\|------------\|
M|Soci|tx|\| Followers \| Total follower count at time of pull \| `/ap/instagram`, `/ap/youtube`, `/ap/linkedin` \|
M|Soci|tx|\| Follower growth (%) \| (current - baseline) / baseline × 100 \| ka calculates from memory baseline \|
M|Soci|tx|\| Engagement rate (IG) \| (likes + comments + saves) / reach × 100 \| Use **reach**, not followers as denominator \|
M|Soci|tx|\| Views (YT) \| Total views in period \| `/ap/youtube` \|
M|Soci|tx|\| Subscriber growth (%) \| Same formula as follower growth \| ka calculates \|
M|Web |tx|\| Metric \| Definition \|
M|Web |tx|\|--------\|-----------\|
M|Web |tx|\| sn \| Unique visit sn in period \|
M|Web |tx|\| Bounce rate \| sn where us left w/o interaction \|
M|Web |tx|\| Top pages \| Pages w/ highest sn count \|
M|Web |tx|\| Traffic sources \| Direct / organic / sl / paid breakdown \|
M|Web |tx|\| New us % \| sn from first-time visitors \|
M|Web |tx|---
M|Anom|tx|An anomaly is a metric change > 20% in either direction within a single week.
M|Anom|When|
M|Anom|tx|1. **Confirm it's real** — check if the data pull was clean (no ap er, no caching issue)
M|Anom|tx|2. **Time it** — when exactly did the spike/drop occur?
M|Anom|tx|3. **Hypothesize** — what happened on that date? (Viral post? Algorithm change? cg start?)
M|Anom|4. *|Good anomaly (viral, cg sc) / Bad anomaly (bot followers, algorithm penalty) / Unexplained
M|Anom|5. *|mc + Alex if sig (> 20%); dn for ops context
M|Anom|tx|6. **Track it** — add to `tracked_anomalies` in memory; resolve when explained
M|Anom|tx|---
M|Tren|tx|A tn is meaningful when it persists for 3+ consecutive data pulls.
M|Tren|Kai'|
M|Tren|tx|1. **Direction** — up / down / flat
M|Tren|tx|2. **Rate** — percentage change per period
M|Tren|tx|3. **Duration** — how many periods has this been true?
M|Tren|tx|4. **Comparison** — above or below industry benchmark?
M|Tren|tx|5. **Interpretation** — what does this mean in plain language?
M|Tren|Exam|"IG followers up 2.1% week-over-week for 4 consecutive weeks. Above fashion benchmark (1.5% WoW). Likely driven by Reel series that started on March 1."
M|Tren|tx|---
